1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,680
PREVIOUS EPISODE

2
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:39,360
Why were Chit and Chaiya
shooting at each other?

3
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:42,000
Chaiya and Manat are drug dealers.

4
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:43,240
<i>What's going on?</i>

5
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:45,360
Why are the cops suddenly the bad guys?

6
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:47,080
Their connections and power

7
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:48,640
can make anything happen.

8
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:50,640
What's this tape?

9
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:52,200
It's a home video.

10
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:54,640
Your mom loved filming and keeping these.

11
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:57,080
<i>I'll name you</i>

12
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:58,520
<i>Puna.</i>

13
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:02,480
The person who died
in the car 20 years ago

14
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:05,440
wasn't your dad. It was Uncle Tharin.

15
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:08,400
I have both my mom and dad

16
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,680
always by my side.

17
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:12,360
It really is Chart.

18
00:03:12,440 --> 00:03:15,200
I think they're following us
to kill us again.

19
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:33,040
Today, I won't kill you.

20
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,160
Because Wilai asked me not to.

21
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:37,520
Next time, no promises.

22
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,040
Mom, what are you doing?

23
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,960
Fixing your phone, sweetie.

24
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:57,840
Still not working yet.

25
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,840
Can I have one to play with?
I want to check the news.

26
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:04,320
Take mine then.

27
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:05,920
Go ahead.

28
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:10,600
This is really tricky.

29
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:14,120
BREAKING! YOUNG POLICE OFFICERS
LINKED TO DRUG TRAFFICKING CASE

30
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,480
Why is this happening?

31
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:17,600
How can this news be real?

32
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,600
What's going on? You're so loud.

33
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:24,640
Dad! There's news online

34
00:04:24,720 --> 00:04:26,440
that Chaiya and Manat

35
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:28,040
are drug dealers!

36
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,400
BREAKING! YOUNG POLICE OFFICERS
LINKED TO DRUG TRAFFICKING CASE

37
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,600
That Manat, the one who helped us?

38
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:37,600
I never thought
he'd turn out to be a bad guy.

39
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,960
Don't jump to conclusions

40
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:42,760
from online news.
There's so much fake stuff out there.

41
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,920
If it's fake, why would they post it?

42
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,720
Hey! If he is a drug dealer,

43
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,960
wouldn't killing you in the woods
be way easier for him?

44
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:54,320
That's true, Dad.

45
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,800
I don't know!

46
00:04:57,680 --> 00:05:00,800
If it turns out he really is the criminal,

47
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,760
we'll be in trouble.

48
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,760
BREAKING! YOUNG POLICE OFFICERS
LINKED TO DRUG TRAFFICKING CASE

49
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,680
Ugh.

50
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:17,640
-What a pain. What?
-Auntie!

51
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:20,200
Why are you shouting so much?

52
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:24,440
Seriously, learn some manners!

53
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:25,960
Why are you yelling? I'm right here!

54
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:27,680
Oh my gosh!

55
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:30,280
Manat, Chaiya.

56
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:32,640
They're all drug dealers?

57
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:37,480
Both cops and drug dealers,

58
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:39,360
they're so hardworking!

59
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:42,360
Hardworking? They're clearly criminals!

60
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:43,960
Whoa! Good looks,

61
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:46,520
but a terrible personality.

62
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,800
No wonder every time they look at me,

63
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:50,600
their eyes are full of lust.

64
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:51,920
Who?

65
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,400
Them, looking at me!

66
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:57,400
Really, it's true!

67
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:59,640
How do you see me? I'm serious.

68
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:01,480
Let me tell you.

69
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:02,880
Every time they look at me,

70
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:04,920
it's full of intent,

71
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,800
like they're inviting me
to become their prey.

72
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,480
Prey?

73
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,680
Prey.

74
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:14,360
-What?
-Sexual prey!

75
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:15,840
Haven't you heard of it? Sexual prey.

76
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:17,120
-How?
-Really!

77
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:19,800
See, both Manat

78
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:22,040
and Chaiya were chasing me.

79
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:24,360
Lucky me, I got to choose,

80
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:26,360
not just anyone.

81
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,960
<i>Mr. Singha.</i>

82
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:34,120
That woman with the headscarf
came to see Tharin.

83
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:37,360
I saw her face clearly. I'm sure

84
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:39,080
that she's Onanong.

85
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:43,960
Also, Tharin fought me
and knocked me down.

86
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,440
Most importantly,

87
00:06:45,960 --> 00:06:47,520
his leg isn't injured.

88
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,200
Phupha.

89
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,320
It really is the two of them.

90
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:53,800
Finally,

91
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,280
they've shown themselves.

92
00:06:59,000 --> 00:06:59,960
Chart!

93
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:01,720
Yes, Mr. Singha.

94
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,680
Catch them and bring them to me.

95
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,080
Tod.

96
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:08,600
Yes, Chart.

97
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:11,040
You're going to handle this.
The boss sent an order.

98
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:12,840
Understood.

99
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,040
Let's hide here.

100
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,160
No one should be able to find us.

101
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:38,480
It's so far out.
How are you going to get food?

102
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:41,760
You go see Aunt Sroi

103
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:44,800
and tell her to cook for us once a day.

104
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:47,240
She's the only one who knows the place.

105
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,160
Got it.

106
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:52,960
Take care of Puna too, okay?

107
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:55,360
But if things look risky,

108
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:57,760
bring her here to us right away.

109
00:07:57,840 --> 00:07:59,200
Don't worry.

110
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:01,160
I'll take care of her.

111
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:08,040
-Thank you so much, Teacher.
-Yes.

112
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:25,960
-How's it going?
-Chart.

113
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,920
I already searched his house.

114
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,840
I didn't find Onanong or Phupha at all.

115
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:33,120
How is that possible?

116
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,520
Did they realize it beforehand?

117
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:38,640
Geez, Phupha!

118
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,960
Onanong!

119
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:45,720
They got away?

120
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:49,280
Yes, they realized it in time
and managed to get away.

121
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:54,280
This puts us at a disadvantage.

122
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:57,720
The tape is in their hands.
The statute of limitations isn't over yet.

123
00:08:57,800 --> 00:09:00,720
If they could file it, we're finished!

124
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,960
What if…

125
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:13,040
What if we manage to capture Puna?

126
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:17,480
We have to catch Puna.

127
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:19,040
If she's in our hands,

128
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:21,280
we hold the leverage.

129
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:24,000
The game changes immediately.

130
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,040
Puna.

131
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:34,240
<i>Darling, listen to me</i>
<i>I have something to say</i>

132
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:39,600
<i>Pay close attention</i>
<i>Hear every word I give</i>

133
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:43,120
<i>The love I offer you</i>

134
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,720
Mr. Sonrak.

135
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,640
Today you seem really distracted.

136
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:48,120
Are you feeling unwell?

137
00:09:48,920 --> 00:09:50,720
I think that's enough for today.

138
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:53,160
But we still need to shoot the MV.

139
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,040
Please stop.

140
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,440
Teacher.

141
00:09:57,480 --> 00:10:00,360
Can I have a moment?
I'll talk to him myself.

142
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:02,080
Okay.

143
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:08,960
You're completely unfocused.

144
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:11,640
I can't stop thinking about Puna.

145
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:16,520
I love you, Sonrak.

146
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:19,600
I can't stand seeing you so miserable.

147
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,800
I miss Puna, Dad.

148
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,640
But she doesn't care about me at all.

149
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:29,440
She only cares about Chaiya.

150
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:30,920
I won't accept it, Dad.

151
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,960
I will never lose to Chaiya.

152
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:34,880
Alright.

153
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,560
I'll bring Puna to you.

154
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:38,800
Really, Dad?

155
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,080
You're not joking, are you?

156
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:42,840
I'm not joking.

157
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,920
But you need to focus on your work.

158
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:48,120
Then you'll get what you want.

159
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,880
You're going to bring Puna to me?

160
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:53,120
Dad, I…

161
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,400
I want to marry Puna, Dad.

162
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,960
Once you have her,
you don't need to marry her.

163
00:10:58,040 --> 00:10:59,640
Why take a girl like this so seriously?

164
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,200
No, Dad! I'm serious.

165
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,960
I'll never lose to Chaiya!

166
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:04,880
Please, Dad. I want to marry Puna.

167
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:07,000
In my life, I'll marry only Puna.

168
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,160
Please, Dad.

169
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:10,680
Please help me.

170
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:15,000
Please help me, Dad.

171
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,920
I want to marry Puna.

172
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:24,320
No matter

173
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:27,280
how much time passes,

174
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:31,560
you will always be my little angel.

175
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:34,200
I love you, Puna.

176
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:40,080
Even if one day

177
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:43,600
you learn the truth

178
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:46,600
that I hid many things from you,

179
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:50,000
I want you to know one thing.

180
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:54,040
Everything I've done in my life

181
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:56,840
has been for you

182
00:11:57,880 --> 00:11:59,760
and for your father, Phupha.

183
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:23,160
Why are you standing here, Wilai?

184
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,000
Looks like

185
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:31,400
-you're crying.
-No, no.

186
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:35,200
It's just my eyes stinging.

187
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:41,960
Tharin.
Can I ask you something?

188
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:44,120
What is it?

189
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:45,720
What do you think,

190
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:48,160
how does Phupha

191
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:51,240
feel about the song "Soft Heart"?

192
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:54,400
I'm not really sure.

193
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:57,000
But as far as I know,

194
00:12:57,520 --> 00:13:00,120
Phupha really loves that song.

195
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:04,320
Every time he listens to it, he cries.

196
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,720
If I were him…

197
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:13,600
I probably couldn't tell

198
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:18,160
whether it's sadness or anger
from being abandoned by his wife.

199
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,840
So for me…

200
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:24,560
"Soft Heart"

201
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:27,920
is more like a memorial of sorrow

202
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,840
and deep pain.

203
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:33,560
Then why does Phupha

204
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:36,960
keep that tape of "Soft Heart"?

205
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,680
I don't really know.

206
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:42,200
For me,

207
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:45,560
everything

208
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:47,600
that comes from love

209
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,600
and from someone we love

210
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:53,920
is precious.

211
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:58,200
No matter how small
or insignificant it seems,

212
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:03,200
I would keep it safe just as it is,

213
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:06,480
unchanged.

214
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,760
What are you wishing for, Puna?

215
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:31,960
I wish to find the tape.

216
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:35,000
And I wish that goodness

217
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:36,680
will triumph over evil.

218
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:40,920
That's right.

219
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,600
If good people lose today,

220
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:45,640
then what's the point of being good?

221
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:48,320
Teacher.

222
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:50,240
Even if I lose,

223
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:52,760
I will still be good.

224
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:56,160
Not to beat anyone,

225
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:59,000
but for my own heart.

226
00:15:00,040 --> 00:15:01,920
Even if I don't find the tape,

227
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:06,200
I'll still fight in my own way.

228
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:08,640
I'll fight to the very end.

229
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:12,000
I pray that your purity

230
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:16,040
will protect you always, Puna.

231
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:26,480
Hello.

232
00:15:27,640 --> 00:15:29,200
This is Teacher Mueangphrai speaking.

233
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,280
Sure.

234
00:15:34,480 --> 00:15:36,000
Right now?

235
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:38,560
But I'm not very good at speaking.

236
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:46,080
-Who was that?
-A TV show.

237
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:50,640
Sonrak just released his single,

238
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:52,200
"My Request",

239
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:54,320
and it's getting popular.

240
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:56,400
They want to interview the songwriter.

241
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,720
I never imagined, Puna.

242
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:01,240
A reporter is coming to interview me.

243
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:03,760
Congratulations, Teacher!

244
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:05,760
Now you're officially recognized.

245
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:10,240
It took a while to get here.
I'm getting old.

246
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:13,680
Want to come with me, Puna?

247
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:17,160
No, Teacher. I'm with a different label.

248
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:20,200
If I go with you, it could cause conflict.

249
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:21,720
But I'm worried about you.

250
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:23,600
It's okay, Teacher.

251
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:26,400
If anyone was following,
we'd have seen them by now.

252
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:28,320
The company's close. I can go back myself.

253
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,640
Then let's part ways here.

254
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:31,560
Good luck!

255
00:16:36,760 --> 00:16:37,760
You can do it!

256
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:01,720
I feel uneasy leaving Puna alone.

257
00:17:12,319 --> 00:17:13,440
Chaiya.

258
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:16,880
Put your gun away.

259
00:17:28,359 --> 00:17:29,520
Hello, Deputy Chief.

260
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:31,440
Your case isn't ordinary.

261
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,960
National-level politicians

262
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:35,720
are involved now.

263
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:38,760
Everything's getting distorted
in the chaos.

264
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:40,080
From being an anti-drug officer,

265
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:42,560
I've been turned into a drug dealer.

266
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:45,080
I'm completely unprepared, sir.

267
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:46,800
I'm working on a way to help you.

268
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:48,320
Be patient.

269
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:51,320
But if you get arrested,
don't resist, no matter what.

270
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:54,640
They want to kill you
in a staged encounter to close the case.

271
00:17:54,720 --> 00:17:55,720
Don't fall for it.

272
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,280
Yes, sir.

273
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:06,480
Remember,

274
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:09,640
good people never lose.

275
00:18:10,280 --> 00:18:11,440
Yes.

276
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:35,360
Deputy Chief Phuchong has gone off.

277
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,480
Now he's alone.

278
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:44,720
Where did Puna go?

279
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,840
Did she already leave?

280
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:02,800
Chaiya?

281
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:03,800
Puna.

282
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:07,920
I didn't expect to see you here.

283
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,200
I came to get a blessing at the temple.
What about you?

284
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:13,200
Come this way.

285
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:24,240
I arranged to meet
a high-ranking officer here.

286
00:19:24,320 --> 00:19:25,640
He promised

287
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:27,600
to help me clear the case I'm accused of.

288
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:31,840
They created false evidence

289
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:33,600
and framed me and Manat,

290
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:35,160
leaving us in a difficult position.

291
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:36,480
News about arrest warrants

292
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:39,720
for you and Manat
are all over the internet right now.

293
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:41,320
Exactly.

294
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:44,040
I can't move around freely.

295
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,640
I had to contact Deputy Chief Phuchong,

296
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:48,080
my superior,

297
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:49,040
to help clear this up.

298
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:51,000
I hope it works.

299
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:54,520
Thank you. Really, thank you.

300
00:19:56,440 --> 00:19:57,960
How will we stay in touch?

301
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:01,400
I have a number,

302
00:20:01,960 --> 00:20:03,520
but only use it for emergencies.

303
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:05,320
Give me your phone.

304
00:20:10,640 --> 00:20:12,320
Use this number to contact me.

305
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:14,880
But I can't call often,
or I might get caught.

306
00:20:14,960 --> 00:20:17,120
Okay. I'll use it only when necessary.

307
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:19,000
I'm going now.

308
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,560
Take good care of yourself.

309
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:48,520
Soon,

310
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:51,280
I'll come back and take care of you.

311
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:19,000
Hands up and surrender!
Don't even think about running.

312
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:20,840
The police have surrounded the place.

313
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:22,440
Chaiya!

314
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:25,680
Hey! Where are you going? Come with me!

315
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:30,760
Put the handcuffs on!
What are you standing there for?

316
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:33,200
Don't struggle!

317
00:21:44,560 --> 00:21:46,800
Acting tough, huh? Go!

318
00:21:51,640 --> 00:21:52,760
Puna!

319
00:21:53,680 --> 00:21:54,720
Puna!

320
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:58,560
Puna!

321
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:01,120
Help! Puna!

322
00:22:08,320 --> 00:22:09,440
Help!

323
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:10,800
Someone, please help!

324
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:11,720
Puna!

325
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:18,560
Kamnan!

326
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:20,480
Kamnan!

327
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:23,600
Is Kamnan Pong here?

328
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:25,160
He isn't here.

329
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:27,000
Hey, where did he go?

330
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:28,760
Just now, Captain Tom called.

331
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:32,240
Mr. Chaiya is in danger,
so he went to help.

332
00:22:37,120 --> 00:22:38,320
What happened?

333
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:40,720
Both Chaiya and Puna…

334
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:48,280
-Go!
-Where are you taking me?

335
00:22:48,360 --> 00:22:49,520
Just walk!

336
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:51,480
Sit down!

337
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:54,320
What are you going to do?

338
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:55,800
Shut you up for good.

339
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:58,920
You're dead.

340
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:21,880
-Don't follow them.
-Why, Chaiya?

341
00:23:21,960 --> 00:23:24,360
Right now, Manat and I
aren't police officers.

342
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:26,440
Even if we catch them,
it would still be illegal.

343
00:23:27,520 --> 00:23:30,360
Exactly. They'll definitely be suspicious
about who came to help us.

344
00:23:31,640 --> 00:23:33,280
Let them be suspicious.

345
00:23:33,360 --> 00:23:35,200
The people I use

346
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:37,520
aren't from around here anyway.
Let's get out of here.

347
00:23:58,280 --> 00:23:59,800
Why are you doing this?

348
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:04,400
Don't play innocent. I know all this time

349
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:06,600
you planned to steal my teddy bear.

350
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:09,960
I was stupid not to realize
there was something hidden inside.

351
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:14,560
Onanong hid the tape, didn't she?

352
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:16,760
Yes!

353
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:19,920
Now we have the tape
exposing your wrongdoing.

354
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,360
Let me go right now!

355
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:23,400
If you want to survive,

356
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:24,960
hand over that tape.

357
00:24:25,680 --> 00:24:26,760
Where is it?

358
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:30,800
It's with Mueangphrai, isn't it?

359
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:33,160
It's not with him.

360
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:34,640
Then where is it? Tell me.

361
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:37,080
I'll never tell you.

362
00:24:37,160 --> 00:24:38,160
Fine.

363
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:40,800
Then you'll regret it.

364
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:50,120
Who are you? What are you doing here?

365
00:24:51,120 --> 00:24:53,160
Where are Phupha
and that ghost-faced woman?

366
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:02,120
Are you okay, Tharin?

367
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:07,280
I miss Puna.

368
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:12,960
Puna is lucky

369
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:14,560
to have an uncle like you.

370
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:22,160
I don't understand myself either,

371
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:24,840
why I love

372
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:27,520
and worry for Puna so much.

373
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:30,320
Even though I'm just an uncle.

374
00:25:32,120 --> 00:25:35,320
The bond, the love, the connection.

375
00:25:36,280 --> 00:25:37,240
What was that?

376
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:42,720
I mean, you've raised her
since she was a child.

377
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:46,880
Naturally, there's a bond, love, and care.

378
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:49,280
It's only natural to worry.

379
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:54,680
I believe

380
00:25:54,760 --> 00:25:56,640
Puna will be safe.

381
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:58,440
I feel the same way.

382
00:26:03,120 --> 00:26:05,160
-Grab them!
-No!

383
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:07,320
If you do, I'll call the police!

384
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:10,040
Call the police?

385
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:15,440
You're going to call the police?

386
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:20,240
Gunshot!

387
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:22,240
Sroi, Saijai!

388
00:26:22,320 --> 00:26:23,160
Let's go!

389
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:30,240
Tell me! Where is Phupha?

390
00:26:30,320 --> 00:26:33,120
Please don't hurt us. I beg you!

391
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,600
I said tell me!

392
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:39,800
Where is Phupha?!

393
00:26:40,520 --> 00:26:42,000
We don't know!

394
00:26:45,760 --> 00:26:47,160
Watch out.

395
00:26:47,240 --> 00:26:48,080
Yes.

396
00:26:56,360 --> 00:26:57,960
Do you want to die?

397
00:26:58,040 --> 00:27:00,360
Where's Phupha?

398
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:02,600
I'm right here!

399
00:27:04,720 --> 00:27:05,640
-Take cover!
-Saijai!

400
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:06,960
You bastards from hell!

401
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:37,160
This way!

402
00:27:37,240 --> 00:27:38,400
-Hurry!
-Let's go!

403
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:02,320
Kitti.

404
00:28:02,840 --> 00:28:04,680
Where are you rushing off to?

405
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:06,760
Onanong,

406
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:09,160
our beautiful singer.

407
00:28:13,480 --> 00:28:15,200
That's your past.

408
00:28:16,160 --> 00:28:19,080
But I like your face in the present more.

409
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,560
-Come with me.
-Let go!

410
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:41,240
You know what to do.

411
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:43,120
-Yes.
-Yes.

412
00:28:46,160 --> 00:28:47,280
Go!

413
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:49,840
Go!

414
00:28:54,840 --> 00:28:56,000
Chart!

415
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:58,560
You destroyed my family.

416
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:01,000
You shouldn't even exist!

417
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:02,560
Drop the gun!

418
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:05,280
Or she dies!

419
00:29:12,600 --> 00:29:14,280
-Drop it!
-Wilai.

420
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,440
Quick!

421
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:31,560
-Hey!
-No!

422
00:29:46,080 --> 00:29:48,640
What?
They've taken her already?

423
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:51,520
Yes. Saijai, Aunt Sroi's daughter,

424
00:29:51,600 --> 00:29:53,040
just called to tell us.

425
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:56,920
They're going to kill my sister
and my niece for sure!

426
00:29:57,800 --> 00:30:00,160
Kamnan, help Puna and Onanong!

427
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:03,720
Okay. I'll definitely help.

428
00:30:11,840 --> 00:30:13,320
Aren't you overthinking this,

429
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:14,520
setting up a trap?

430
00:30:14,600 --> 00:30:16,000
I have a feeling

431
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:17,520
that sooner or later,

432
00:30:17,600 --> 00:30:18,680
they'll find us.

433
00:30:19,680 --> 00:30:22,200
Better to prepare than to do nothing.

434
00:30:24,440 --> 00:30:27,440
Hey. Did you call Sergeant Au yet?

435
00:30:27,520 --> 00:30:29,320
I told him to stand by at the car already.

436
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,720
Then, when we get the signal,

437
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:33,160
let him pick us up immediately.

438
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:38,080
Who's calling?

439
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:41,920
Deputy Chief.

440
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:46,080
Yes, Deputy Chief.

441
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:48,240
Where are you right now?

442
00:30:52,400 --> 00:30:54,200
Did you hear me?

443
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:01,040
Send me the location.

444
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:02,600
I'll come to you.

445
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:05,120
Yes, sir.

446
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:07,400
I'll send it via the same chat.

447
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:16,400
Thank you very much, Deputy Chief.

448
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:19,800
Chaiya just sent the location.

449
00:31:21,160 --> 00:31:22,720
Send it to me immediately.

450
00:31:23,320 --> 00:31:25,160
I'm waiting to meet them.

451
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:28,240
We don't have much time left, Manat. Go.

452
00:31:28,320 --> 00:31:29,240
Hurry.

453
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:37,200
Let's go.

454
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:42,080
Looks like you understand better now,

455
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:45,600
what should be done

456
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:48,000
and what shouldn't.

457
00:31:49,560 --> 00:31:50,560
Well…

458
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:52,240
You deserve a reward.

459
00:31:52,320 --> 00:31:53,360
No need.

460
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:56,280
Just don't interfere with me.

461
00:31:57,120 --> 00:31:59,880
Then I'll report to the Minister

462
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:02,560
that you don't want him involved.

463
00:32:12,200 --> 00:32:13,080
Chart.

464
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:16,520
Here it is. The house at the location.

465
00:32:17,280 --> 00:32:18,840
Are you sure this is the right house?

466
00:32:19,680 --> 00:32:20,880
I'm sure.

467
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:23,320
There's only one house around here.

468
00:32:23,400 --> 00:32:25,120
They have to be here.

469
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:26,600
Good.

470
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:29,440
Hey, surround the house. Go!

471
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:39,280
They're here.

472
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:45,160
Are you sure you heard the Morse code
from the pen taps?

473
00:32:45,240 --> 00:32:46,360
I'm sure.

474
00:32:47,200 --> 00:32:48,560
Normally, he wouldn't
do something like this.

475
00:32:49,240 --> 00:32:51,520
The code we got is an SOS signal.

476
00:32:53,040 --> 00:32:54,400
Someone must be with him,

477
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:56,120
forcing him to give our location.

478
00:32:58,640 --> 00:32:59,560
Lure them to the back.

479
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:01,240
Got it, buddy.

480
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:10,840
Yes, it's them. Attack!

481
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:31,800
Go!

482
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:35,680
Ugh! They've escaped!

483
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:36,640
Hey, follow them!

484
00:34:16,199 --> 00:34:18,679
They're dangerous, not easy to deal with.

485
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:20,159
Pull back, Chart.

486
00:34:20,239 --> 00:34:21,080
We'll set another trap.

487
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:24,080
-Let's go.
-Damn it!

488
00:34:35,639 --> 00:34:37,080
Captain, get in the car!

489
00:34:37,520 --> 00:34:39,360
Sergeant Au's here. Let's go!

490
00:34:52,639 --> 00:34:54,040
They got away?

491
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:56,880
It's okay.

492
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:59,400
I have a Plan B for you, Mr. Singha.

493
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:03,840
That's it for now.

494
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:11,880
You called me.

495
00:35:11,960 --> 00:35:13,040
Do you need something?

496
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:15,720
You're ordered to lead the hunt

497
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:17,440
for the criminals.

498
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:19,320
Who?

499
00:35:20,160 --> 00:35:21,840
Chaiya and Manat.

500
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:23,080
What did you say?

501
00:35:23,680 --> 00:35:26,040
You heard right. This case

502
00:35:26,120 --> 00:35:28,080
has clear evidence

503
00:35:28,720 --> 00:35:30,200
that they're drug dealers.

504
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:33,960
I won't mind

505
00:35:34,720 --> 00:35:36,480
if you kill them in the process.

506
00:35:39,240 --> 00:35:40,560
But sir,

507
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:43,200
I haven't seen clear evidence
of drug trafficking yet.

508
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:45,440
That's not your responsibility.

509
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:48,280
You don't need to see the evidence.

510
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:50,000
Just take the order and lead the unit

511
00:35:50,080 --> 00:35:52,480
to catch these two criminals.

512
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:56,240
-I'm concerned that--
-Don't be difficult.

513
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:58,320
Your duty

514
00:35:58,400 --> 00:36:00,040
is to capture them quickly.

515
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:02,440
I'll close the case.

516
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:06,840
Yes, sir.

517
00:36:30,240 --> 00:36:31,360
Wilai.

518
00:36:31,440 --> 00:36:32,440
You're awake.

519
00:36:35,320 --> 00:36:36,840
Take it slow.

520
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:39,640
Are you safe?

521
00:36:39,720 --> 00:36:40,960
I'm fine.

522
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:42,800
They shot you,

523
00:36:43,720 --> 00:36:45,640
then locked us up here.

524
00:36:47,840 --> 00:36:48,680
Puna?

525
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:53,000
I haven't heard anything about Puna.

526
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:55,000
I don't know

527
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:58,560
what's happening to her.

528
00:36:58,640 --> 00:36:59,640
I have no idea.

529
00:37:01,400 --> 00:37:02,560
Those bastards.

530
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:29,240
We've got those two.
Where are they being held?

531
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:30,640
At the farmhouse.

532
00:37:31,240 --> 00:37:33,320
It's my safe house. I've got my men

533
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:34,840
watching them.

534
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:36,000
Good.

535
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:38,640
Hey, what about the tape?

536
00:37:39,520 --> 00:37:40,880
Did you find it?

537
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:42,120
No.

538
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:43,840
I searched them myself.

539
00:37:43,920 --> 00:37:46,200
The tape wasn't on them.

540
00:37:46,280 --> 00:37:47,920
I searched the house they were hiding in.

541
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:49,160
Still no tape.

542
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:51,720
They must've hidden it somewhere.

543
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:58,960
Did they hand it over to the police?

544
00:37:59,040 --> 00:38:01,120
Calm down, Singha.

545
00:38:01,200 --> 00:38:03,560
No matter what,
we still have the upper hand.

546
00:38:04,320 --> 00:38:05,560
What do you mean?

547
00:38:05,640 --> 00:38:07,920
We still have Puna.

548
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:10,440
If they use the tape to threaten us,

549
00:38:11,080 --> 00:38:12,480
we'll use Puna

550
00:38:12,560 --> 00:38:14,480
to threaten them back. That's all.

551
00:38:14,560 --> 00:38:16,360
We can't do that!

552
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:18,200
Puna's a singer now.

553
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:20,920
If we do that,
things will get way out of hand.

554
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:23,720
Then,

555
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:26,760
we make it a family matter.

556
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:29,600
Outsiders won't be able to interfere.

557
00:38:30,320 --> 00:38:31,560
Family matter?

558
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:33,840
How do we do that?

559
00:38:34,600 --> 00:38:36,520
Well, Sonrak

560
00:38:36,600 --> 00:38:40,080
wants to marry Puna anyway, doesn't he?

561
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,720
We'll just make them get married.

562
00:38:44,360 --> 00:38:47,360
Then Puna becomes part of the family.

563
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:51,640
And if the media tries to pry

564
00:38:51,720 --> 00:38:53,280
into our business,

565
00:38:53,360 --> 00:38:55,240
we can just say

566
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:58,040
it's a family matter.

567
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:01,760
No!

568
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:04,640
I won't marry Sonrak.

569
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:06,280
No matter what happens, I refuse!

570
00:39:06,880 --> 00:39:07,960
Why?

571
00:39:08,040 --> 00:39:09,400
What's wrong with Sonrak?

572
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:10,920
Why can't you marry him?

573
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:13,040
I don't love him.

574
00:39:13,120 --> 00:39:15,040
I already have someone I love.

575
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:16,520
Chaiya, right?

576
00:39:18,640 --> 00:39:20,680
A criminal on the run like him,

577
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:21,800
it won't be long

578
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:24,080
before he's caught,
if he doesn't get killed.

579
00:39:24,680 --> 00:39:25,600
That's not true!

580
00:39:26,360 --> 00:39:27,840
The one who should be caught

581
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:28,920
is you, not him.

582
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:38,480
Don't you want to see your parents again?

583
00:39:41,240 --> 00:39:43,640
Hey, what do you mean by that?

584
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:46,280
That means,

585
00:39:47,120 --> 00:39:49,200
right now, I've captured Wilai

586
00:39:49,280 --> 00:39:50,440
and Tharin,

587
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:54,360
who are your real parents.

588
00:39:57,440 --> 00:40:00,120
Whether they live or die,

589
00:40:00,680 --> 00:40:02,120
it depends on you.

590
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:07,600
Where did you take my parents?

591
00:40:14,240 --> 00:40:17,280
You'll get to see them for sure

592
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:18,920
on your wedding day.

593
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:21,880
After we become one family,

594
00:40:21,960 --> 00:40:25,360
I'll forget all the grudges from the past.

595
00:40:25,440 --> 00:40:27,080
Decide carefully, Puna.

596
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:29,320
Only you

597
00:40:30,920 --> 00:40:32,200
can make this

598
00:40:32,280 --> 00:40:34,720
end well.

599
00:41:03,160 --> 00:41:04,720
Coffee, Mr. Sonrak.

600
00:41:12,640 --> 00:41:14,200
Mr. Sonrak.

601
00:41:14,280 --> 00:41:16,360
Right now, your new song

602
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:18,040
is really popular.

603
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:20,960
On TikTok, everyone is covering it.

604
00:41:22,160 --> 00:41:23,800
Aunt Riam, you use TikTok too?

605
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:25,640
Of course! These days,

606
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:26,720
if you don't,

607
00:41:26,800 --> 00:41:28,560
you're really missing out.

608
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:30,800
Yes.

609
00:41:42,040 --> 00:41:44,240
You want to marry Puna, right?

610
00:41:45,080 --> 00:41:48,080
Go ahead and ask her. She could say yes.

611
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:09,920
Puna.

612
00:42:11,120 --> 00:42:12,000
Wait.

613
00:42:12,520 --> 00:42:14,000
How did you get here?

614
00:42:19,800 --> 00:42:21,640
Why don't you ask Puna, Sonrak?

615
00:42:21,720 --> 00:42:22,880
About our recent conversation.

616
00:42:33,160 --> 00:42:34,560
Puna, well…

617
00:42:36,040 --> 00:42:38,560
I know we haven't known each other long,

618
00:42:40,040 --> 00:42:42,640
and I've hurt you before.

619
00:42:42,720 --> 00:42:44,800
But I want you to know

620
00:42:44,880 --> 00:42:47,360
that I'm just as sorry.

621
00:42:47,960 --> 00:42:49,000
So today,

622
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:52,680
I want to ask you for a chance.

623
00:42:54,640 --> 00:42:55,760
Puna.

624
00:42:56,920 --> 00:42:58,160
I…

625
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:02,600
Will you marry me?

626
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:06,120
What's your answer, Puna?

627
00:43:08,320 --> 00:43:10,160
Will you accept or refuse?

628
00:43:10,240 --> 00:43:13,160
It's all to you.

629
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:30,600
Puna, it's okay.

630
00:43:30,680 --> 00:43:32,560
It's okay, Puna.

631
00:43:33,160 --> 00:43:35,040
I understand.

632
00:43:35,120 --> 00:43:37,680
Gaining a woman's trust is never easy.

633
00:43:38,480 --> 00:43:40,160
If you're not willing,

634
00:43:40,240 --> 00:43:41,880
that's fine. I understand.

635
00:43:45,720 --> 00:43:47,040
Yes, Mr. Sonrak.

636
00:43:51,080 --> 00:43:52,960
I'll marry you.

637
00:43:56,560 --> 00:43:58,880
I will marry you, Mr. Sonrak.

638
00:44:01,440 --> 00:44:02,720
Really, Puna?

639
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:11,120
You said it!

640
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:18,880
You said it, Puna.

641
00:44:23,160 --> 00:44:24,440
Thank you.

642
00:44:25,440 --> 00:44:27,800
Thank you for giving me a chance.

643
00:44:28,840 --> 00:44:30,480
I love you, Puna.

644
00:44:32,200 --> 00:44:34,040
Thank you, Puna.

645
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:44,520
Dad! Look at this!

646
00:44:44,600 --> 00:44:46,680
What is it, dear?
Did someone break into our house?

647
00:44:46,760 --> 00:44:48,560
No, Mom.

648
00:44:48,640 --> 00:44:51,240
The news says Puna agreed
to marry Mr. Sonrak, Dad!

649
00:44:51,920 --> 00:44:53,600
What kind of nonsense is this?

650
00:44:53,680 --> 00:44:55,160
How could she go marry him?

651
00:44:56,200 --> 00:44:57,160
Maybe it's because the news

652
00:44:57,880 --> 00:45:00,400
says Chaiya and Manat are drug dealers.

653
00:45:00,480 --> 00:45:02,000
That's why Puna changed her mind.

654
00:45:02,080 --> 00:45:03,640
Typical people,

655
00:45:03,720 --> 00:45:05,960
reading the news without any analysis.

656
00:45:08,160 --> 00:45:11,040
Analyze what?

657
00:45:11,520 --> 00:45:12,680
The reporters must have verified it.

658
00:45:13,400 --> 00:45:15,120
Otherwise, how could they publish it?

659
00:45:22,880 --> 00:45:23,880
Puna.

660
00:45:31,800 --> 00:45:33,160
Why did it turn out this way?

661
00:45:47,880 --> 00:45:51,040
From now on, Puna will stay
with us at the house.

662
00:45:51,120 --> 00:45:53,200
I asked Aunt Riam
to prepare the guest room.

663
00:45:54,200 --> 00:45:55,880
Thank you, Dad.

664
00:45:57,480 --> 00:45:59,040
That's good, Puna.

665
00:45:59,120 --> 00:46:01,040
This way, we'll have more time together.

666
00:46:04,040 --> 00:46:05,520
Puna.

667
00:46:05,600 --> 00:46:06,960
Is something wrong?

668
00:46:07,560 --> 00:46:10,360
Why don't you look very happy?

669
00:46:11,720 --> 00:46:13,120
That's normal, Sonrak.

670
00:46:13,960 --> 00:46:16,280
A woman has to know
how to keep her composure.

671
00:46:16,360 --> 00:46:19,480
Showing too much joy isn't always good.

672
00:46:19,560 --> 00:46:20,440
Right, Puna?

673
00:46:23,160 --> 00:46:24,200
Yes.

674
00:46:24,280 --> 00:46:25,760
About the wedding,

675
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:27,960
I want you two

676
00:46:28,560 --> 00:46:31,640
to get married as soon as possible.
Any problems, Sonrak?

677
00:46:31,720 --> 00:46:34,840
How soon, exactly?

678
00:46:35,440 --> 00:46:36,680
Next week.

679
00:46:38,240 --> 00:46:39,440
Whoa!

680
00:46:39,520 --> 00:46:41,880
Dad, isn't that too fast?

681
00:46:41,960 --> 00:46:43,920
My new single just came out,

682
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:45,480
and I already have work lined up.

683
00:46:45,560 --> 00:46:47,120
Work can wait.

684
00:46:47,200 --> 00:46:50,440
Handle it after the wedding.
Getting married as soon as possible,

685
00:46:50,520 --> 00:46:52,800
that's Puna's condition.

686
00:46:52,880 --> 00:46:54,040
She wants to marry quickly.

687
00:46:54,120 --> 00:46:55,560
Right, Puna?

688
00:46:59,080 --> 00:46:59,920
Yes.

689
00:47:01,400 --> 00:47:04,560
If that's what Puna wants,
I have no problem with it, Dad.

690
00:47:08,720 --> 00:47:11,200
The room is ready for you.

691
00:47:12,400 --> 00:47:14,600
Let's go. I'll take you
to the room. Come on.

692
00:47:14,680 --> 00:47:15,680
It's okay.

693
00:47:16,240 --> 00:47:18,560
I can go with Aunt Riam.

694
00:47:18,640 --> 00:47:19,840
Okay.

695
00:47:19,920 --> 00:47:21,600
I'll follow you.

696
00:47:24,440 --> 00:47:25,680
This way, please.

697
00:47:30,760 --> 00:47:32,080
Dad, I mean…

698
00:47:32,160 --> 00:47:33,520
How did you do it?

699
00:47:33,600 --> 00:47:35,880
How did you get Puna to agree so easily?

700
00:47:35,960 --> 00:47:38,560
Everything I did was for you.

701
00:47:38,640 --> 00:47:39,760
You…

702
00:47:40,560 --> 00:47:42,560
don't need to know how.

703
00:47:42,640 --> 00:47:43,680
Dad.

704
00:47:45,760 --> 00:47:47,240
Thank you so much.

705
00:47:48,040 --> 00:47:49,680
I love you, Dad.

706
00:47:50,560 --> 00:47:52,480
I love you very much too, Sonrak.

707
00:47:53,080 --> 00:47:56,120
I want you to have everything you desire.

708
00:48:10,200 --> 00:48:12,880
I pray to the sacred spirits.

709
00:48:12,960 --> 00:48:15,840
Please protect and watch over

710
00:48:15,920 --> 00:48:18,440
my parents.

711
00:48:19,040 --> 00:48:21,520
Please don't let anything happen to them.

712
00:48:23,440 --> 00:48:25,600
And let me have the chance

713
00:48:26,200 --> 00:48:29,400
to hug them once more.

714
00:48:38,160 --> 00:48:39,440
Chaiya!

715
00:48:39,520 --> 00:48:40,360
<i>Come with me.</i>

716
00:48:40,440 --> 00:48:41,960
Split up and find Puna! Go!

717
00:48:42,040 --> 00:48:42,880
NEXT EPISODE

718
00:48:42,960 --> 00:48:45,240
No matter what happens tomorrow,
let's decide

719
00:48:45,320 --> 00:48:48,360
with our own hearts today.

720
00:48:48,440 --> 00:48:50,000
<i>If I disappear,</i>

721
00:48:50,080 --> 00:48:52,240
<i>they definitely won't keep</i>
<i>my parents alive.</i>

722
00:48:52,320 --> 00:48:54,480
Chaiya! It's Chaiya, Dad!

723
00:48:54,560 --> 00:48:56,000
Superintendent, I need your help.

724
00:48:56,840 --> 00:48:59,960
Don't move. There's an order to kill.

725
00:49:00,040 --> 00:49:01,400
Whether you are Phupha

726
00:49:01,480 --> 00:49:04,120
or Tharin, the time has come

727
00:49:04,200 --> 00:49:06,600
for me to tell you the truth.

728
00:52:06,480 --> 00:52:08,480
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
